{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse by initiating partial restitution. While the offense is a breach of fiduciary trust, a multi-year sentence is disproportionate to the crime and the spectator's outburst is an irrelevant emotional appeal that does not influence legal sentencing guidelines. A period of incarceration followed by supervised probation is appropriate to balance rehabilitation with punishment.",
  "verdict": 6
}
